A RALLY was held in Glasgow in support of Home Rule Covenant that has attracted close to 5,000 signatories. March has a message on Scots powers as city pub changes name to Yesbar A RALLY was held in Glasgow in support of Home Rule Covenant that has attracted close to 5,000 signatories.More than 100 people braved yesterday's bad weather in a march aimed at Lord Smith of Kelvin - the man entrusted to deliver greater powers to Holyrood.Meanwhile, city centre bar Vespbar announced it will permanently change its name to Yesbar from November 5. 